               <head>Sharḥ-i Yūsūf va Zulaykhā by ʻAbd al-Vāsiʻ Hānsavī</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2010105563">
                  <summary>A Persian commentary on <title>Yūsuf va Zulaykhā</title> (also known as
                        <title>Maḥabbat-nāmah</title>) of <persName role="ant" key="VIAF_90042997"
                        >Nūr al-Dīn ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Jāmī</persName> (1414-92), written by ʻAbd
                     al-Vāsiʻ Hānsavī (d. 1706-07) </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1251-item1">
                     <author key="VIAF_118045836">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʻAbd al-Vāsiʻ Hānsavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">عبد الواسع هانسوی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23476">Sharḥ-i Yūsūf va Zulaykhā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">شرح یوسف و زلیخا</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa"> محبوب‌ترین مقالات شرح قصه ستایش جمال یوسفی
                        است</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"> بدون یاء تنکیر باضافت آن بجانب خاموشی</explicit>
                     <colophon>(f. 76v) Completed in the middle of Tuesday, 8 Jumada I 1252 AH (23
                        August 1836) by <persName role="scr" key="person_f8596">Prānah/Pirānah?</persName> in the <hi
                           rend="italic">qaṣbah</hi> of Hisar. </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>After 10 lines in f.2r, the text is left unwritten, leaving ff.2v, 3r,
                           and 12 lines of 3v blank. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
